race.comment: JOTOPELI (2) has been racing in great heart with two top-three finishes on end, the latest a second over 1600m at Murtoa when he was in the firing line all the way. Has the ability to figure prominently. SAXON BLOOD (4) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1240m at Geelong, beaten 42 lengths. Beautifully placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. PARKRUN (3) was prominent at the turn and finished third last time over 1562m at Mt Gambier, beaten 3 lengths. Nicely placed to take this out. BLOW ON THE DICE (10) produced a fair effort on debut last time out when fourth at Hamilton over 1400m. Comes into calculations.
